cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper deals with visual localization, which is a problem in computer vision and robotics. The paper proposes a novel approach that learns an implicit representation of the environment at a higher, more abstract level, for instance that of objects. This approach involves the use of Generative Query Networks (GQNs) and attention mechanisms. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). 

The paper also deals with robotics and localization, which suggests that it could belong to cs.RO (Robotics). The use of GQNs and attention mechanisms involves machine learning techniques, which suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper proposes a novel approach to the problem of visual localization, which suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper deals with the representation of 3D scenes, which suggests that it could belong to cs.GR (Graphics).
